Seems that this is a **bug** ([JDK-6480539](https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-6480539)) which was fixed in **Java 8** (per OpenJDK commit [2ee772cda1d6](http://hg.openjdk.java.net/jdk8/jdk8/jdk/rev/2ee772cda1d6)).

Workaround for earlier versions of Java:

```lang-java
BigDecimal zero = BigDecimal.ZERO;
if (someBigDecimal.compareTo(zero) == 0) {
    someBigDecimal = zero;
} else {
    someBigDecimal = someBigDecimal.stripTrailingZeros();
}
```

I sadly can&#39;t help you with the task of playing videos continuously.

But for your problem of randomizing the List here are some some food for thought. If you have a collection `col` you can use `Collections.shuffle(col)` to shuffle their entries.

    List&lt;Integer&gt; waitingArray = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

    waitingArray.add(R.raw.d41);
    waitingArray.add(R.raw.d42);
    waitingArray.add(R.raw.d43);
    Collections.shuffle(waitingArray);

That might suffice if i would need a list of three entries shuffled for a single usage.

Taking into consideration your other problem of looping the videos I could imagine that you would want your list of video continue in an unpredictable manner.

One way would be to create a bag of all possible videos and shuffle it an pull the elements one by one, until the bag is empty. And only then refill it randomly again. This is how the [tetrominoes][1] [modern versions of Tetris][2] are distributed.

    public class RandomBag&lt;T&gt;
    {
        private final Collection&lt;T&gt; sources;
        private List&lt;T&gt; currentBag = Collections.emptyList();
    
        public RandomBag(Collection&lt;T&gt; sources)
        {
            this.sources = sources;
        }
    
        public synchronized T get()
        {
            if (currentBag.isEmpty())
            {
                createNewBag();
            }
            currentBag.get(0);
        }
    
        private void createNewBag()
        {
            currentBag = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(sources);
            Collections.shuffle(currentBag);
        }
    }


  [1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetromino
  [2]: http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/interview/11267/tetris-from-the-top-an-interview-with-henk-rogers

